com.dlsc.flexgantt.util

Class FlexGanttLicenseManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dlsc.flexgantt.util.FlexGanttLicenseManager

  • public final class FlexGanttLicenseManager
extends Object
    Handles anything related to licensing. The license key needs to be set by calling setLicenseKey(String). If no license key has been set then FlexGantt will enter trial / evaluation mode.
    Since:
    1.1
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.8 $
    Author:
    Dirk Lemmermann

        public static void setLicenseKey(String key)
        Sets the license key used for FlexGantt. The key determines whether the product uses a development or a runtime license.
        Parameters:
        key - the license key
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the license key gets set more than once
        Since:

      • getVersion

        public static String getVersion()
        Returns the product version (e.g. "1", "1", ...). This number is the version number used for licensing issues only. It represents the major version number. A more detailed version number can be looked up by calling Version.getVersion().
        Returns:
        the product version
        Since:
        1.1
